title: Contributing to b3gbi
text: want make bigger change, ’s good idea first file issue make sure someone team agrees ’s needed. ’ve found bug, please file issue illustrates bug minimal reprex (also help write unit test, needed). See guide create great issue advice.

title: Contributing to b3gbi
text: Fork package clone onto computer. haven’t done , recommend using usethis::create_from_github("b-cubed-eu/b3gbi", fork = TRUE). Install development dependencies devtools::install_dev_deps(), make sure package passes R CMD check running devtools::check(). R CMD check doesn’t pass cleanly, ’s good idea ask help continuing. Create Git branch pull request (PR). recommend using usethis::pr_init("brief-description--change"). Make changes, commit git, create PR running usethis::pr_push(), following prompts browser. title PR briefly describe change. body PR contain Fixes #issue-number. user-facing changes, add bullet top NEWS.md (.e. just first header). Follow style described https://style.tidyverse.org/news.html.

title: Contributing to b3gbi
text: New code follow tidyverse style guide. can use styler package apply styles, please don’t restyle code nothing PR. use roxygen2, Markdown syntax, documentation. use testthat unit tests. Contributions test cases included easier accept.

title: Tutorial
text: Let’s look core functions b3gbi package. first one called process_cube() used import GBIF occurrence cubes .csv files R objects. simple use. need provide name location cube .csv format. Note different versions GBIF cubes floating around, format changed. Since code package created present generation came available, compatible old new cubes. old ones come additional .csv file containing taxonomic information cube. type name cube object, contents displayed custom print function within package. can see object structure using str(). cube contained tibble (tidyverse version data frame) called data, variables contain metadata. Now let’s look indicators available calculate plot. indicators registered ones actually working package. others, fully functional moment registered. available indicator listed along class, functions used calculate map /time series. next function need understand called compute_indicator_workflow(). core package, work calculating indicator done. indicator comes wrapper functions, used rather directly calling compute_indicator_workflow(). wrapper functions listed . type name indicator object, see plotted internal function package. cube objects, indicator objects contain tibble called data. case mapped indicator, tibble also sf object containing geometry information cell. indicator object belongs two specialized object classes determine handled use plot() command. First, either class ‘indicator_ts’ ‘indicator_map’. Second, class specific indicator type. can see using class() command. S3 classes (S3 one several objected oriented programming systems contained within R). final functions need interface plot functions. plot_ts() plot_map(), fact called using plot(). plot functions offer quite arguments customize output, plotting done using ggplot package, customization quite easy.   additional functions package can make use , list_species(), lists species contained cube indicator object, mostly quite simple. continued…

Uses the whole cube by default. #   * Argument 6: region (optional), the name of the region to calculate over (e.g. Germany, Europe). Uses the whole cube by default. #   * Argument 7: cube_crs (optional), the projection the cube uses if not LAEA # Outputs: #   * indicator_ts or indicator_map object containing a data frame of indicator values mapped to years or grid cells, along with various metadata. #   * total_occ_ts(): Calculate the total number of records over time #   * occ_density_map(): Calculate the density of records over a gridded map #   * occ_density_ts(): Calculate the density of records over time #   * williams_eveness_map(): Calculate Williams' evenness over a gridded map #   * williams_evenness_ts(): Calculate Williams' evenness over time #   * pielou_evenness_map(): Calculate Pielou's evenness over a gridded map #   * pielou_evenness_ts(): Calculate Pielou's evenness over time #   * ab_rarity_map(): Calculate abundance-based rarity over a gridded map #   * ab_rarity_ts(): Calculate abundance-based rarity over time #   * area_rarity_map(): Calculate area-based rarity over a gridded map #   * area_rarity_ts(): Calculate area-based rarity over time #   * newness_map(): Calculate the mean year of occurrence over a gridded map #   * newness_ts(): Calculate the mean year of occurrence over time #                        # Example: library(b3gbi) Europe_observed_richness_map <- obs_richness_map(example_cube_2, first_year = 1980)  #> Warning: Unknown or uninitialised column: `num_species`. #> Warning: Unknown or uninitialised column: `num_families`. #> Warning: Unknown or uninitialised column: `kingdoms`. Called by plot(). # Inputs:  #   * Argument 1: x, an indicator_ts object  #   * Argument 2: title (optional), specify a title for the plot #   * Argument 3: auto_title (optional), specified by the calling function if title is set to "auto" #   * Argument 4: y_label_default (optional), specified by the calling function if no y_label is provided #   * Argument 5: suppress_y (optional), default is "FALSE". Set to "TRUE" to turn off y axis text #   * Argument 6: smoothed_trend (optional), default is "TRUE". Set to "FALSE" to avoid displaying only the time series, without a smoothed trend  #   * Argument 7: linecolour (optional), sets the colour of the unsmoothed time series line #   * Argument 8: trendlinecolour (optional), sets the colour of the smoothed trend line  #   * Argument 9: envelopecolour (optional), sets the colour of smoothed trend envelope #   * Argument 10: gridoff (optional), default is "FALSE". Set to "TRUE" to turn off grid lines on the plot   #   * Argument 11: x_label (optional), use to set a custom label for the x-axis #   * Argument 12: y_label (optional), use to set a custom label for the y-axis #   * Argument 13: min_year (optional), set the first year that will be plotted #   * Argument 14: max_year (optional), set the final year that will be plotted #   * Argument 15: x_breaks (optional), set the number of breaks along the x-axis #   * Argument 16: y_breaks (optional), set the number of breaks along the y-axis #   * Argument 17: wrap_length (optional), set maximum length of text allowed on a single line for the plot title # Outputs: #   * Time series plot with optional smoothed trend overlay. The plot can be further customized (beyond the provided arguments) using ggplot functions. #   * Plots can be saved using ggsave.  # Example: library(b3gbi) Europe_observed_richness_ts <- obs_richness_ts(example_cube_2, first_year = 1980)  #> Warning: Unknown or uninitialised column: `num_species`. #> Warning: Unknown or uninitialised column: `num_families`. #> Warning: Unknown or uninitialised column: `kingdoms`. plot(Europe_observed_richness_ts) # Function 4: plot_map() # Description: Plots an indicator_map object as a gridded map using ggplot. Called by plot(). # Inputs:  #   * Argument 1: x, an indicator_map object  #   * Argument 2: title (optional), specify a title for the plot #   * Argument 3: auto_title (optional), specified by the calling function if title is set to "auto" #   * Argument 4: leg_label_default (optional), legend title specified by the calling function if no leg_label is provided #   * Argument 5: xlims (optional), use to set custom map limits #   * Argument 6: ylims (optional), use to set custom map limits  #   * Argument 7: trans (optional), set transformation to apply to the legend, e.g. "log10" #   * Argument 8: breaks (optional), set custom breaks for the legend #   * Argument 9: labels (optional), set custom labels for the legend #   * Argument 10: Europe_crop (optional), default is "TRUE". title: General Biodiversity Indicators for Biodiversity Data Cubes
text: Biodiversity researchers need robust standardized tools analyze vast amounts data available platforms like GBIF. b3gbi package leverages power data cubes streamline biodiversity assessments. helps researchers gain insights : Changes Time: biodiversity metrics shift throughout years. Spatial Variations: Differences biodiversity across regions, identifying hotspots areas concern. Impact Factors: different environmental variables human activities might affect biodiversity patterns.

title: General Biodiversity Indicators for Biodiversity Data Cubes
text: b3gbi empowers biodiversity analysis : Standardized Workflows: Simplify process calculating common biodiversity indicators GBIF data cubes. Flexibility: Calculate richness, evenness, rarity, taxonomic distinctness, Shannon-Hill diversity, Simpson-Hill diversity, . Analysis Options: Explore temporal trends create spatial maps. Visualization Tools: Generate publication-ready plots biodiversity metrics.

title: General Biodiversity Indicators for Biodiversity Data Cubes
text: basic example shows calculate plot map species richness data cube containing GBIF occurrence data amphibians Europe:  -depth introduction, see tutorial: https://b-cubed-eu.github.io/b3gbi/articles/b3gbi.html.
code: # Load package library(b3gbi)  # Load GBIF data cube cube_name <- system.file("extdata", "europe_insect_cube.csv", package = "b3gbi")  # Load taxonomic info for cube tax_info <- system.file("extdata", "europe_insect_info.csv", package = "b3gbi")  # Prepare cube insect_data <- process_cube(cube_name, tax_info)  # Calculate diversity metric map_obs_rich_insects <- obs_richness_map(insect_data)  # Plot diversity metric plot(map_obs_rich_insects, title = "Observed Species Richness: Insects in Europe")

title: Calculate Biodiversity Indicators Over Space or Time — compute_indicator_workflow
text: data data cube object (class 'processed_cube'). type indicator calculate. Supported options include: 'obs_richness': Observed species richness. 'total_occ': Total number occurrences. 'newness': Mean year occurrence. 'density': Density occurrences. 'williams_evenness', 'pielou_evenness': Evenness measures. 'ab_rarity', 'area_rarity':  Abundance-based area-based rarity scores. dim_type Dimension calculate indicator (time: 'ts', space: 'map') cell_size Length grid cell sides, km. (Default: 10 country, 100 continent world) level Spatial level: 'continent', 'country', 'world'. (Default: 'continent') region region interest (e.g., "Europe"). (Default: "Europe") cube_crs projection cube. (Default: "EPSG:3035") first_year Exclude data year. (Uses data cube default.) last_year Exclude data year. (Uses data cube default.) ... Additional arguments passed specific indicator calculation functions.
